_width = min(min_width, dp[k][j])\n                    count += min_width\n        \n        return count\n```\n\nThis solution works by first constructing a helper array `dp` where `dp[i][j]` contains the number of consecutive 1s ending at position `(i, j)`. Then, for each cell in the matrix, it considers that cell as the bottom-right corner of a potential rectangle and counts all possible rectangles that can be formed with this cell as the bottom-right corner, considering all possible heights. The time complexity of this solution is O(m * n^2), which is efficient enough given the problem constraints.", "estimated_date": 1593907200000}